i would love good brown rice sushi recipes i've looked on the internet but i always find the best answers here scant cup short grain brown rice cup plus teaspoon water teaspoons soy sauce tablespoons seasoned rice vinegar teaspoon wasabi powder by inch sheets roasted nori dried laver kirby cucumber peeled seeded and cut into inch thick matchsticks carrot cut into inch thick matchsticks firm ripe small california avocado oz radish sprouts roots trimmed special equipment a bamboo sushi mat accompaniments soy sauce for dipping sliced gari pickled ginger preparation rinse rice well and bring to a boil with cup water and teaspoon soy sauce in a to quart heavy saucepan then reduce heat to very low and simmer tightly covered until water is absorbed about minutes remove from heat and let rice stand covered minutes while rice is standing stir together vinegar and remaining teaspoon soy sauce transfer rice to a wide nonmetal bowl preferably wood ceramic or glass and sprinkle with vinegar mixture tossing gently with a large spoon to combine cool rice tossing occasionally about minutes stir together wasabi and remaining teaspoon water to form a stiff paste let stand at least minutes to allow flavors to develop place sushi mat on a work surface with slats running crosswise arrange sheet nori shiny side down on mat lining up a long edge of sheet with edge of mat nearest you using damp fingers gently press half of rice about cup onto nori in layer leaving a inch border on side farthest from you arrange half of cucumber in an even strip horizontally across rice starting inch from side nearest you you may need to cut pieces to fit from side to side arrange half of carrot just above cucumber in same manner peel avocado half and cut lengthwise into thin slices then arrange half of slices just above carrot in same manner repeat with radish sprouts letting some sprout tops extend beyond edge beginning with edge nearest you lift mat up with your thumbs holding filling in place with your fingers and fold mat over filling so that upper and lower edges of rice meet then squeeze gently but firmly along length of roll tugging edge of mat farthest from you to tighten nori border will still be flat on mat open mat and roll log forward to seal with nori border moisture from rice will seal roll transfer roll seam side down to a cutting board make second log in same manner then cut each log crosswise into pieces with a wet thin bladed knife serve with wasabi paste soy sauce and ginger Jewish cuisine Casting Hot dog Tea Cookware and bakeware Cuisine of Singapore Brewery Vinegar Ketchup Coffee French fries Wood Mayonnaise Idli Fast bowling Mango Chili con carne Professional wrestling holds Violin Professional wrestling throws Breakfast Bento Chicken soup Menstrual cup Turkish coffee Textile manufacturing terminology Comanche Seismic retrofit Chopsticks Peruvian cuisine Campfire Woodworking Leaf Cuisine of Malaysia Solar cell Flax Rice Pickling Udon Desert Soy milk Potato Cheese Stairway Welding Milk Cuisine of Laos Table tennis Polish cuisine Puff pastry Sugar beet German cuisine Internal ballistics Yerba mate Screw Soy sauce Domesticated turkey Powder metallurgy Cuisine of Brazil Cajun cuisine Potato chips Opportunity rover Jiaozi Pasta Curry Conveyor belt sushi Equine conformation Russian cuisine Sandwich Daikon 